# Forge Project — Cursor Rules

## Project Context
Read CLAUDE.md before every file edit. Read docs/CONVENTIONS.md before writing any code.
Forge is a self-hosted, BYOK, multi-session AI agent workbench. Option B conversation graph architecture.

## File Rules
- All Python files must start with the developer signature header from CONVENTIONS.md
- All TypeScript/TSX files must start with the developer signature header from CONVENTIONS.md
- All functions must have complete docstrings (see CONVENTIONS.md for format)
- Max 300 lines per file, max 50 lines per function
- No logic in __init__.py files — imports and __all__ only
- One class per file unless tightly coupled (e.g., exceptions)

## Behavior Rules
- Only modify files listed in the current task description (tasks/IN_PROGRESS.md)
- If a change requires a new dependency, add it to pyproject.toml AND note it in the task
- Write tests before or alongside implementation, never after separately
- Never create business logic in API route files — put it in services/
- No direct database calls outside db/ layer
- No hardcoded strings — use constants or config
- All async functions must be awaited (no fire-and-forget without Celery)
- Never call LLM provider APIs directly — always go through LiteLLM
- Never use LangChain agents — use LangGraph for orchestration

## Navigation
- API routes: backend/app/api/
- Business logic: backend/app/services/
- LangGraph flows: backend/app/core/
- Pydantic models: backend/app/models/
- Database: backend/app/db/
- Graph (Neo4j): backend/app/graph/
- Tools: backend/app/tools/
- Tests: backend/tests/
- Specs: specs/phase-X/
- Tasks: tasks/
- Architecture: docs/ARCHITECTURE.md
- Conventions: docs/CONVENTIONS.md

## Import Ordering
1. Standard library imports
2. Third-party imports
3. Local application imports
Each group separated by a blank line. Alphabetical within groups.

## Naming Conventions
- Python files: snake_case.py
- Python classes: PascalCase
- Python functions: snake_case
- Python constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
- TypeScript files: kebab-case.ts / kebab-case.tsx
- React components: PascalCase
- API route files: snake_case.py
- Environment variables: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
- Database tables: snake_case
- Neo4j node labels: PascalCase
- Feature branches: feature/FXXX-short-description
- Fix branches: fix/FXXX-short-description

## Commit Messages
Use Conventional Commits format:
```
type(scope): short description

[optional body]
[optional footer]
```
Types: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, test, chore, ci

## Error Handling
- Use custom exception classes from backend/app/core/exceptions.py
- Never catch bare `except:` — always specify the exception type
- Log errors with structured logging (structlog)
- Return appropriate HTTP status codes from API handlers
- Include correlation IDs in error responses

## When in Doubt
Read the spec file. The spec is the authority.
Check docs/ARCHITECTURE.md for system design questions.
Check docs/CONVENTIONS.md for code style questions.

## TURN.md
Update TURN.md as your first and last action in every response.
